AU  - Fulghieri, Paolo
T1  - Entrepreneurial Finance and Innovation: An Introduction and Agenda for Future Research
PY  - 2014
Y1  - 2014/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hht063
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 27
IS  - 1
SP  - 1
EP  - 19
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - The increasingly large role played by financial intermediaries, such as venture capitalists and angels, in nurturing entrepreneurial firms and in promoting product market innovation has led to great research interest in the area of entrepreneurial finance and innovation. This paper introduces the special issue of the Review of Financial Studies dedicated to entrepreneurial finance and innovation and highlights some of the promising topics for future research in this area. The special issue combines papers presented at the June 2010 “Entrepreneurial Finance and Innovation (EFIC)” conference, which was jointly sponsored by the Kauffman Foundation and the Review of Financial Studies, with other related papers.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hht063
ER  - 



